Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_get_legend(25.10)                                    gui_get_legend(25.10)

Name
       gui_get_legend - Gets the current legend setting

Syntax
        gui_get_legend

       [-help]

       -type  {inst_density pin_density timing_map metal_density route_conges-
       tion temperature}

       [-display_range | -value_range | -show_legend_on_layout | -legend_loca-
       tion | -enable_min_value | -enable_max_value]

       Gets the current legend setting.

       You can use the gui_set_legend and gui_get_legend commands to  get  the
       snapshot of different density for analysis.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man gui_get_legend

       -display_range
              Gets the display range

       -enable_max_value
              Gets the state of the max value of display range.

       -enable_min_value
              Gets the state of the min value of display range.

       -legend_location
              Gets the location of legend.

       -show_legend_on_layout
              Gets the state of legend on layout.

       -type {inst_density pin_density timing_map metal_density route_conges-
       tion temperature}
              Gets the setting for the specified legend type.

       -value_range
              Gets the value range.

Example
       The following command sets the legend for the inst_density legend type:

       >  gui_set_legend  -type inst_density -display_range {1 0.9} -show_leg-
       end_on_layout true

       The following command gets the current legend setting for the inst_den-
       sity legend type.

       > gui_get_legend -type inst_density

       {display_range {0.9 0.9}} {legend_location  ne}  {show_legend_on_layout
       true} {value_range {0.75 1}}

